y the build plugin rather than through Testcontainers itself. I need to check how Docker images are being utilized here.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_BpO9BnLQuTf2REU9Z1RC9Oet|fc_02a92d8c45096df0016a42387d19dc8190b66c05688ffbb244", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"allowed.*docker|docker_image|allowed-docker|Docker\" forge ai_workflows . -g'*.py' -g'*.md' -g'*.json' | head -80", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1245, "output": 636, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35161, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782724722132, "responseId": "resp_02a92d8c45096df0016a423872956881909c426c05781ddeb2"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_BpO9BnLQuTf2REU9Z1RC9Oet|fc_02a92d8c45096df0016a42387d19dc8190b66c05688ffbb244", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "rg: ai_workflows: No such file or directory (os error 2)\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/contributing/questions.json:20:    \"help\": \"Enter the docker images (press enter after each image name you enter) that you want to use in your tests. Docker image declaration consists of two parts separated with \\\":\\\" in the following format: \\\"imageName:version\\\". When you finish adding docker images, type \\\"-\\\" to terminate the inclusion process.\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:311:# Maven Central and Docker registry failures have no such boundary (Gradle owns\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:221:If your tests use Docker (either with explicit Docker process invocation or through some library method call), all images have to be declared in `required-docker-images` file.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:224:Only Docker images that are listed in the [`allowed-docker-images` directory](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images) can be used for testing.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:226:That pull request should add a new file in the [`allowed-docker-images` directory](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images)\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:227:with the name in the format `Dockerfile-<dockerImageName>` (replace all occurrence of `/` with `_`) .\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:236:   * If your test uses Docker image, and you didn't specify it in the `required-docker-images.txt` file, the test will fail.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:237:   * If your test uses Docker image that is not listed in [allowed docker images list](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/AllowedDockerImages.txt),\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:239:   * Only docker images that are in both `required-docker-images.txt` and in the `allowed docker images list`\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:243:See an [example](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/Dockerfile-mysql_mysql-server).\n./docs/tests.md:16:  Docker images it needs in `required-docker-images.txt`, and is the unit the\n./docs/tests.md:59:  declared, pre-pulled `allowed-docker-image` with networking disabled, and\n./docs/e2e.md:17:`pullAllowedDockerImages` for the resolved coordinate, then runs the full infra\n./docs/functional-spec.md:68:- Schedule-driven: full metadata sweep every three days to prevent incomplete or breaking metadata from shipping in releases, new-library-version compatibility (every six hours), Docker image vulnerability scans, scheduled release every Monday, scheduled coverage publication.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:125:| `docker` | PR | PR updates allowed Docker images used by tests. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:232:- **Declared Docker images.** Tests that use Docker must declare every image they need in `required-docker-images.txt`. Each image must already appear in `tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/Dockerfile-<dockerImageName>`. Tests fail otherwise.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:240:- **Docker isolation.** Docker images used in tests are pre-pulled from `allowed-docker-images`, after which the runner disables Docker networking for deterministic, isolated test runs.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:244:- **Docker tag sync.** Dependabot updates to `allowed-docker-images` trigger `sync-docker-tags.yml`, which back-commits the synchronized tags into the Dependabot PR.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:259:- **Determinism.** Tests must be reproducible. Network-dependent tests are not allowed except where they declare an `allowed-docker-image` and run against that pre-pulled image with networking disabled.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:332:`./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages checkMetadataFiles test -Pcoordinates=<group:artifact:version>`.\n./docs/tck.md:98:## 6. Docker image management\n./docs/tck.md:102:| `pullAllowedDockerImages` | Pre-pull only the images a coordinate's metadata allows, before networking is disabled for isolated runs (§FS-repository-functional-spec.5.3). |\n./docs/tck.md:103:| `checkAllowedDockerImages` | Scan allowed images for vulnerabilities with grype, either all images or only those changed between two commits (§CI-scan-docker-images). |\nforge/utility_scripts/library_preparation_preflight.py:44:LIBRARY_PREFLIGHT_DETERMINISTIC_KINDS = (\"dependency\", \"docker_image\")\nforge/utility_scripts/library_preparation_preflight.py:55:    \"tests\", \"tck-build-logic\", \"src\", \"main\", \"resources\", \"allowed-docker-images\"\nforge/utility_scripts/library_preparation_preflight.py:285:    if kind == \"docker_image\":\nforge/utility_scripts/library_preparation_preflight.py:365:        \"The setup can be one of three things: an extra Maven dependency, a Docker \"\nforge/utility_scripts/library_preparation_preflight.py:367:        \"must set. Represent d